cript-wait">waitForever</a></code>, <code><a href="https://davidwalsh.name/waitfortime">waitForTime</a></code>...</a></code></p></div></li><li data-url="https://davidwalsh.name/querylocalfonts" itemscope itemtype=http://schema.org/Article><div class=meta>By <a href="http://davidwalsh.name" rel=author itemprop=author itemscope itemtype=https://schema.org/Person><span itemprop=name>David Walsh</span></a><time itemprop=datePublished>August 11, 2023</time></div><span itemscope itemtype=https://schema.org/ImageObject><img data-src="/demo/css3logo250.jpg?preview" class=post-image alt="queryLocalFonts" /></span><div class=preview><h2 itemprop=name><a href="https://davidwalsh.name/querylocalfonts" itemprop=url>queryLocalFonts</a></h2><p>One of the larger downloads when requesting a webpage are custom fonts. There are many great techniques for lazy loading fonts to improve performance for those on poor connections.  By getting insight into what fonts the user has available, we can avoid loading custom fonts.</a></code></p></div></li><li data-url="https://davidwalsh.name/xhr-fetch-breakpoints" itemscope itemtype=http://schema.org/Article><div class=meta>By <a href="http://davidwalsh.name" rel=author itemprop=author itemscope itemtype=https://schema.org/Person><span itemprop=name>David Walsh</span></a><time itemprop=datePublished>August 7, 2023</time></div><span itemscope itemtype=https://schema.org/ImageObject><img data-src="https://davidwalsh.name/demo/2023/08/create-xhr-breakpoint.png?preview" class=post-image alt="Use XHR/fetch Breakpoints!" /></span><div class=preview><h2 itemprop=name><a href="https://davidwalsh.name/xhr-fetch-breakpoints" itemprop=url>Use XHR/fetch&nbsp;Breakpoints!</a></h2><p>Web debugging tools are so incredibly excellent these days.  I remember the days where they didn't exist and debugging was a total nightmare, even for the simplest of problems.  A while back I introduced many of you to <a href="https://davidwalsh.name/logpoints">Logpoints</a>, a w